1
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,760
Hello, Major Crimes Unit.

2
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:25,719
Don't be scared, just a few questions.

3
00:00:26,519 --> 00:00:28,440
Do many people usually buy this beer?

4
00:00:29,079 --> 00:00:29,960
Not really that many.

5
00:00:30,359 --> 00:00:31,519
After all, it's a bit pricey.

6
00:00:32,079 --> 00:00:33,200
Then on the night of the 23rd,

7
00:00:33,439 --> 00:00:34,439
that is, last night,

8
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,679
between 10 and 11 PM,

9
00:00:35,679 --> 00:00:36,719
did anyone buy this beer?

10
00:00:36,719 --> 00:00:38,880
That... I honestly can't remember.

11
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,719
Is this surveillance camera working?

12
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,159
Yes, it's working normally.

13
00:00:45,439 --> 00:00:46,679
The footage is stored for a week.

14
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:53,600
Linglong Road, Yifu Convenience Store.

15
00:00:53,759 --> 00:00:54,439
Get over here right away.

16
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:50,000
You're coughing this badly,

17
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,079
maybe cut down on the smoking.

18
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,280
I'm a wreck anyway.

19
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,519
Why bother worrying?

20
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,719
Yesterday, from this trash can,

21
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:05,359
did you pick up a beer can like this?

22
00:02:06,599 --> 00:02:09,080
I pick up tons of cans every night.

23
00:02:09,319 --> 00:02:10,039
I don't remember.

24
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:12,080
Fair enough.

25
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,680
Is your foot injured,

26
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,560
or do you always walk like that?

27
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:21,680
Don't even get me started.

28
00:02:23,319 --> 00:02:25,960
Last night some lunatic on a motorbike

29
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,439
knocked me down.

30
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,120
Right at the alley entrance.

31
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,120
Could you tell if it was a man or woman?

32
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:40,479
By the build, it was a man.

33
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,840
Dressed all in black.

34
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:44,479
But here's the strange part:

35
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:45,879
a grown man,

36
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,879
wearing a pair of red gloves.

37
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:51,000
You're saying he wore red gloves?

38
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,439
Yeah, bright red ones.

39
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:58,280
Shifu.

40
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:00,960
Shifu.

41
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:05,360
Go to the convenience store.

42
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,919
Pull up the surveillance footage.

43
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,680
See if anyone bought this kind of beer.

44
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:10,879
Got it.

45
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:19,039
Captain Li.

46
00:03:19,639 --> 00:03:20,879
Not only was he covered up tightly,

47
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,400
he also kept his face away from the cameras.

48
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,840
But one thing is certain:

49
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:26,719
He bought the exact beer from the scene.

50
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,120
The thing is, this guy wore black gloves.

51
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,240
And a very ordinary style, too.

52
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:32,199
Our case

53
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,759
has something to do with gloves.

54
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,319
Pull up Ma Shijiang's photo for me.

55
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,039
Right.

56
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,080
Security! Mad dog! Beat it to death!

57
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:15,039
Get away!

58
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,399
Get out!

59
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,000
Try that again!

60
00:04:19,439 --> 00:04:20,639
Try it! Try it and I'll hit you!

61
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,959
Who are you to butt in?

62
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:24,360
What did this dog ever do to you?

63
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,279
Why beat it to death?

64
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:26,319
Sticking your nose in, huh?

65
00:04:26,439 --> 00:04:27,560
Step closer and I'll hit you too!

66
00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:31,199
What's going on?

67
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:34,879
Shifu.

68
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,959
These two

69
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:40,240
are officers from the city bureau.

70
00:04:42,759 --> 00:04:43,680
My apologies, Captain Li.

71
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:44,800
President Su.

72
00:04:46,199 --> 00:04:47,240
That dog seemed

73
00:04:48,439 --> 00:04:49,279
to recognize you.

74
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,319
Oh, it's just a stray.

75
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,279
I fed it now and then,

76
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,040
and it latched onto me.

77
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:58,399
Bites you if you don't feed it.

78
00:04:59,079 --> 00:05:00,680
That dog seemed pretty smart to me.

79
00:05:01,079 --> 00:05:02,160
It meant you no harm.

80
00:05:02,319 --> 00:05:03,439
Why insist on beating it to death?

81
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,519
Officer,

82
00:05:06,879 --> 00:05:08,079
this is a bank.

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,040
Lots of customers come in every day.

84
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,759
If that mad dog bit someone,

85
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,480
that'd be real trouble, right?

86
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,639
It didn't look rabid to me.

87
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,160
Probably just hungry.

88
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,120
If it comes back next time,

89
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,040
let it go.

90
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:24,319
Sure, whatever you say, Captain Li.

91
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,879
Come on, let's talk in my office.

92
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:28,279
I've got some fine Dragon Well tea.

93
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:28,920
We can drink while

94
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,759
Let's just talk here.

95
00:05:30,759 --> 00:05:31,519
Just a couple of questions.

96
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:34,360
On the 23rd, between 9 PM and midnight,

97
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:35,920
where were you?

98
00:05:40,199 --> 00:05:41,160
What's that supposed to mean?

99
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:42,879
You suspect

100
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,360
I'm involved in Shen Qing's death?

101
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:46,959
Don't be nervous.

102
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,800
This is just a routine inquiry.

103
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,480
What would I be nervous about?

104
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,680
I just think

105
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,199
your questions are absolutely absurd.

106
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,759
You have the right not to answer.

107
00:05:59,759 --> 00:06:00,399
Captain Li,

108
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,439
Your investigation,

109
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,920
I fully support it.

110
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:05,560
But I won't accept

111
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,639
groundless suspicion.

112
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:09,519
Excuse me, I need to get back to work.

113
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:12,160
If you refuse to be questioned,

114
00:06:12,519 --> 00:06:14,399
we'll have reason to suspect a cover-up.

115
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,680
And we'll launch a deeper investigation.

116
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,120
Are you threatening me?

117
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,920
Let me be perfectly clear:

118
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:28,720
Shen Qing's death

119
00:06:29,079 --> 00:06:30,920
has nothing to do with me.

120
00:06:31,639 --> 00:06:32,920
If you don't believe me,

121
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,319
go ahead and investigate.

122
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:36,360
At 10:25,

123
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,240
didn't Shen Qing call you?

124
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,560
What did you two talk about?

125
00:06:50,439 --> 00:06:51,920
Oh, so that's what this is about.

126
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:53,680
That's right.

127
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:57,000
Shen Qing did call me that night.

128
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:59,199
But she was the credit department head.

129
00:06:59,839 --> 00:07:02,360
We had many phone exchanges every day.

130
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,120
What's unusual about that?

131
00:07:04,399 --> 00:07:05,519
Didn't you just say

132
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,600
this was a routine inquiry?

133
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,600
I'm sorry, Captain Li.

134
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:24,079
I shouldn't have hidden this.

135
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,519
But I didn't do it on purpose.

136
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,319
These past few days...

137
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:33,240
I've been blaming myself too.

138
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:35,000
Because of the Chengming Machinery loan,

139
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,279
headquarters set up an investigation team.

140
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,319
Director Shen was very worried.

141
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,360
That's why she called me that night.

142
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,000
On the phone,

143
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,720
she was extremely unstable.

144
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:50,319
But I never thought she'd end her life.

145
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:51,839
Otherwise,

146
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:54,600
I'd have done everything to stop her.

147
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,040
So your conclusion is

148
00:07:57,639 --> 00:07:59,879
that Shen Qing couldn't cope

149
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,439
and took her own life?

150
00:08:03,959 --> 00:08:05,680
That's just my opinion.

151
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,519
As for the rest,

152
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:10,160
you'll have to investigate further.

153
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,680
Sorry, everyone.

154
00:08:13,079 --> 00:08:14,160
I really have to get to work.

155
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,680
Shifu.

156
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:22,720
This Su Zhuang isn't just cunning,

157
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,279
he's also extremely calculating.

158
00:08:25,199 --> 00:08:26,920
Every time we asked a key question,

159
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:28,319
he cleverly dodged it.

160
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,759
I'm certain

161
00:08:30,199 --> 00:08:31,680
he knows the truth of Shen Qing's death.

162
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:32,919
Your certainty won't help.

163
00:08:34,519 --> 00:08:35,519
Only when we find evidence

164
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,799
will he actually talk.

165
00:08:55,759 --> 00:08:56,440
A Tai

166
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,000
Meet me at the cabin

167
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:13,559
Godfather.

168
00:09:13,759 --> 00:09:14,279
Sit.

169
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:16,840
A Tai...

170
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:20,480
Economic Crimes Unit, Major Crimes Unit...

171
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:22,120
they all have their eyes on me now.

172
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:25,559
I don't care how you do it.

173
00:09:25,919 --> 00:09:27,600
Find Wu Chengming as soon as possible.

174
00:09:28,679 --> 00:09:29,960
And get our money

175
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,960
back.

176
00:09:32,679 --> 00:09:33,639
Don't worry, Godfather.

177
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,080
The second shot.

178
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,480
How's that dog bite healing?

179
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,320
Thank you, Godfather.

180
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,200
All done.

181
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:51,840
I'll be going then.

182
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:53,960
What's the rush?

183
00:09:55,159 --> 00:09:56,240
Such fine tea...

184
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,600
It'd be a waste not to drink it.

185
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:58,360
Come on.

186
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:10,960
Oh, A Tai...

187
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,600
How many years have you been with me?

188
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,240
Five years and three months.

189
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,720
How time flies.

190
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,000
Back then I'd just become bank president.

191
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:27,399
You know what, A Tai?

192
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:29,080
In this world,

193
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,039
there's no shortage of men like me.

194
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:32,559
But what's rare

195
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:34,519
is someone like you.

196
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,679
All these years following me,

197
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,200
doing so much without complaint.

198
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,960
I've kept it all in mind.

199
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,960
We're very close to the goal now.

200
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:50,679
What's mine

201
00:10:51,279 --> 00:10:52,240
is yours.

202
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:55,519
Thank you, Godfather.

203
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:56,840
Off you go.

204
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,360
You're Su Zhuang's wife, right?

205
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,360
We're from the Major Crimes Unit.

206
00:11:14,519 --> 00:11:15,399
We've got a few questions for you.

207
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:17,919
Please come in.

208
00:11:24,639 --> 00:11:25,919
I know about this case.

209
00:11:26,679 --> 00:11:28,320
Does it have to do with my husband?

210
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,000
Don't read too much into it.

211
00:11:30,159 --> 00:11:31,320
This is just routine.

212
00:11:31,639 --> 00:11:33,279
We want to ask about that night.

213
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,720
So please tell us in detail.

214
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,919
Honey, you're home.

215
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,879
Still up this late?

216
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:51,000
Working overtime so late every day.

217
00:11:51,279 --> 00:11:51,919
You must be hungry.

218
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:53,240
I made you a late-night snack.

219
00:11:54,519 --> 00:11:56,080
My wife knows me best.

220
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,320
I really am a bit hungry.

221
00:11:58,639 --> 00:11:59,799
Then go wash your hands.

222
00:12:00,159 --> 00:12:01,120
I'll bring the food out.

223
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:05,240
With all this overtime lately,

224
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:06,919
I've barely had time for you.

225
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,799
Let's open a nice bottle of wine later

226
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,159
and have ourselves a romantic evening.

227
00:12:13,639 --> 00:12:14,200
Mm.

228
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:15,879
Come on, honey.

229
00:12:15,879 --> 00:12:17,759
Have a seat. I'll bring the dishes.

230
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,720
Honey, try the food.

231
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,840
Let me taste my wife's cooking.

232
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,960
Here, try this. Your favorite.

233
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:53,480
Nothing beats a home-cooked meal.

234
00:13:05,159 --> 00:13:06,240
What's wrong?

235
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:09,519
Nothing, I just feel...

236
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:13,320
It's been so long since we sat like this.

237
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:18,600
Here, sweetheart.

238
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,519
All these years,

239
00:13:22,759 --> 00:13:24,080
I've been focused on work.

240
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,360
Rarely had time for you.

241
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:29,600
I'm sorry.

242
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:32,600
Could you try coming home earlier?

243
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,000
I'll cook your favorite dishes.

244
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,919
And we can chat together.

245
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,279
I promise.

246
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:47,879
I've been busy lately

247
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:51,840
because of a tough situation at the bank.

248
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,759
Once this is over,

249
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,159
I'll try to come home early

250
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,600
and spend more time with you.

251
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,120
Come on, cheers.

252
00:14:12,559 --> 00:14:13,600
After drinking,

253
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,679
I felt drunk.

254
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,039
A bit dizzy.

255
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:17,360
So I went to bed.

256
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,519
Do you remember what time you went to bed?

257
00:14:28,759 --> 00:14:31,080
I glanced at the clock during dinner.

258
00:14:31,799 --> 00:14:32,919
9:50.

259
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:36,399
So I was in bed by 10 at the latest.

260
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:39,200
President Su often comes home late, right?

261
00:14:50,399 --> 00:14:51,759
Is this relevant to the case?

262
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,840
I noticed lots of liquor stored at home.

263
00:14:56,279 --> 00:14:57,480
Do you usually like to drink alone?

264
00:14:58,759 --> 00:14:59,559
Occasionally.

265
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:02,200
I'll have a drink when I'm feeling down.

266
00:15:03,399 --> 00:15:04,759
But I'm definitely no alcoholic.

267
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:06,320
Understood.

268
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,360
Then logically,

269
00:15:08,559 --> 00:15:09,840
you must have a good tolerance.

270
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,840
How could one glass of wine get you drunk?

271
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:16,480
It was probably

272
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,360
because I drank it too fast.

273
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,240
So that means that night,

274
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,919
you were asleep by around 10.

275
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:31,159
So you don't know if your husband left?

276
00:15:33,039 --> 00:15:33,679
No.

277
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,759
My husband was home all night.

278
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,039
He was with me the entire time.

279
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,639
Honey.

280
00:15:50,759 --> 00:15:51,440
Honey.

281
00:15:57,399 --> 00:15:59,120
Why did you only sleep for a little while?

282
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:00,360
Honey.

283
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,000
Here, sit down.

284
00:16:04,399 --> 00:16:05,200
What's wrong?

285
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:09,960
It felt like I slept for a long time.

286
00:16:10,799 --> 00:16:13,480
No, you only slept about twenty minutes.

287
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,879
I want some water.

288
00:16:19,679 --> 00:16:21,159
You sit, I'll get it for you.

289
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,919
You woke up in less than half an hour?

290
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,320
I had a nightmare.

291
00:16:32,159 --> 00:16:33,000
In the dream,

292
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:35,360
I heard a loud crash.

293
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,759
It startled me awake.

294
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:39,879
After you woke up, did you feel dizzy?

295
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,200
Probably

296
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,360
because of the nightmare.

297
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,120
Do you remember

298
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,679
him taking a phone call afterward?

299
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:55,080
Here, have some water.

300
00:17:01,919 --> 00:17:03,519
Who's calling so late?

301
00:17:04,759 --> 00:17:05,680
Director Shen.

302
00:17:07,759 --> 00:17:08,960
There's another incident at the bank.

303
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,000
Hey, Director Shen.

304
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,480
What's so urgent at this hour?

305
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,160
Don't panic.

306
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:22,640
I'll explain to the investigation team.

307
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:25,880
No one wants this kind of thing to happen.

308
00:17:29,559 --> 00:17:30,559
As for the money,

309
00:17:30,839 --> 00:17:32,200
I'll find a way to recover it.

310
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:34,680
Anything else,

311
00:17:35,079 --> 00:17:36,359
we'll discuss tomorrow at the office.

312
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,480
So what did you do after that?
